{
  "text": "Furthermore, we analyzed the corresponding nucleotide variation in the African sample. Estimated levels of heterozygosity for 11 fragments are listed in Table 2 . The pattern of polymorphism for loci 4-8 is illustrated in Figure 2b . For fragment 3 we were not able to obtain sequences. With the exception of two low-variation fragments (i.e., loci 6 and 7), the pattern of nucleotide diversity is consistently higher for the African lines (than for the European ones) with an average u of 0.0065 for fragments 4-9 (Figure 1b) . However, this value is 50% lower than the average level of heterozygosity reported for the entire X chromosome in Africa (u \u00bc 0.0127; [CITATION_1] .",
